# Howdy let's do some gene-level RNA-seq analysis in R

We will use the R script above to process the count data from a subset of control frogs from an RNA-seq experiment I ran a few years ago.
Count data was generated using a workflow similar to Pertea et al. 2016 https://doi.org/10.1038/nprot.2016.095 (e.g. hisat2-stringtie-transdecoder2-eggnogmapper)

If you want to see pipeline for transcriptome assembly, annotation, and read counts -- maybe I uploaded it already IDK I can't see into the future

Download and decompress this folder wherever you'd like, best to keep in the biosphere-4 directory from last time.

You'll also need to decompress the annotations "emapper.emapper.zip" (I know the name sucks but I always forget to change in my cluster script)
